cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper uses classical algebraic geometric instruments to process location data of base stations, which involves numerical methods and algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the fitness of log-normal distribution to the Euler characteristics of real base station deployments, which is related to information theory and statistical analysis. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper focuses on the topology of cellular networks, which can be considered as a type of social and information network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper aims to achieve prominent network performances by appropriate placements of base stations, which involves system optimization and control. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper may be relevant to multiagent systems as cellular networks involve multiple agents (i.e., base stations) interacting with each other.
